# Cadre Global Development Standards

## Coding Philosophy

- Prioritize clean, readable, self-documenting code
- Optimize for maintainability, reliability, and impact
- Apply modern, stable tooling (ES Modules, Python 3.11+)

## Languages & Frameworks

- **Languages:** TypeScript, Python, Bash
- **Frameworks:** React, Node.js, Flask/FastAPI
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS
- **Databases:** PostgreSQL > MySQL > MongoDB

## Best Practices

- DRY, KISS, YAGNI principles
- Pure functions and immutability when possible
- Validate and sanitize all user input
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Treat warnings as errors

## Naming Conventions

- **Files:** `lowercase_with_underscores`
- **Variables:** `camelCase`
- **Components/Classes:** `PascalCase`

## Code Style

- Max line length: 100 characters
- Trailing commas for multi-line objects/arrays
- ES Modules only (no `require`)
- Prefer `async/await` over `.then()` chains
- Explicit imports (no wildcards)

## Git Conventions

- Branch names: `{type}/{short-description}`
- Commit format: `type(scope): short summary`
- All work branches from `main`, squash merge
